    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This memo specifies Locator/ID Separation Protocol Security (LISP-SEC), a set of security mechanisms that provides origin authentication, integrity, and anti-replay protection to the LISP's Endpoint-ID-to-Routing-Locator (EID-to-RLOC) mapping data conveyed via the mapping lookup process.  LISP-SEC also enables verification of authorization on EID-Prefix claims in Map-Reply messages.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
